item.description:
This section includes guiding questions and considerations that Project Managers and OSM communities should take into account when beginning a project including:
 Factors to consider when deciding what to map; Contexts that could impact planning and preparation;
 Considerations to make for involving stakeholders, communities, and how to select your team.  Overview When starting a mapping project, it is important to define the scope of the project and understand the larger context in which the data is needed, this includes understanding how to work with local stakeholders and how the data will impact them.

